{"abstract":[{"code":"GPowerProfileMonitor","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" makes it possible for applications as well as OS","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"components to monitor system power profiles and act upon them. It currently","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"only exports whether the system is in “Power Saver” mode (known as"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"“Low Power” mode on some systems).","type":"text"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"PowerProfileMonitorProtocol"},{"text":" : ","kind":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/InitableProtocol","preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO16InitableProtocolP","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"InitableProtocol"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"overview","text":"Overview","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When in “Low Power” mode, it is recommended that applications:"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"disable automatic downloads;"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"reduce the rate of refresh from online sources such as calendar or"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"email synchronisation;"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"reduce the use of expensive visual effects.","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"It is also likely that OS components providing services to applications will","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"lower their own background activity, for the sake of the system.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"There are a variety of tools that exist for power consumption analysis, but those"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"usually depend on the OS and hardware used. On Linux, one could use ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"upower"},{"type":"text","text":" to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"monitor the battery discharge rate, ","type":"text"},{"code":"powertop","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to check on the background activity"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"or activity at all), ","type":"text"},{"code":"sysprof","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to inspect CPU usage, and ","type":"text"},{"code":"intel_gpu_time","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"profile GPU usage."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Don’t forget to disconnect the [signal[Object](\/\/documentation\/gobject\/object\/onnotify(flags:handler:)] signal for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"[property","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/PowerProfileMonitor","isActive":true},{"text":"], and unref the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GPowerProfileMonitor"},{"type":"text","text":" itself when exiting."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/PowerProfileMonitorProtocol","type":"reference"},{"text":" protocol exposes the methods and properties of an underlying ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GPowerProfileMonitor"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The default implementation of these can be found in the protocol extension below."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"For a concrete class that implements these methods and properties, see "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/PowerProfileMonitor","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Alternatively, use "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/PowerProfileMonitorRef","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" as a lighweight, "},{"code":"unowned","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" reference if you already have an instance you just want to use.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/powerprofilemonitorprotocol"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO"]]},"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"metadata":{"fragments":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"PowerProfileMonitorProtocol"}],"roleHeading":"Protocol","modules":[{"name":"GIO"}],"title":"PowerProfileMonitorProtocol","externalID":"s:3GIO27PowerProfileMonitorProtocolP","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"PowerProfileMonitorProtocol"}],"symbolKind":"protocol"},"topicSections":[{"anchor":"Instance-Properties","generated":true,"title":"Instance Properties","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/PowerProfileMonitorProtocol\/powerSaverEnabled","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/PowerProfileMonitorProtocol\/power_profile_monitor_ptr-3snu4"]},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/PowerProfileMonitorProtocol\/bind(property:to:_:flags:transformFrom:transformTo:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/PowerProfileMonitorProtocol\/get(property:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/PowerProfileMonitorProtocol\/getPowerSaverEnabled()","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/PowerProfileMonitorProtocol\/set(property:value:)"],"anchor":"Instance-Methods","generated":true,"title":"Instance Methods"}],"relationshipsSections":[{"kind":"relationships","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/4GLib14PointerWrapperP","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/InitableProtocol"],"type":"inheritsFrom","title":"Inherits From"},{"type":"conformingTypes","kind":"relationships","title":"Conform